<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hide1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hide,</orth> subst. the skin of an animal: <cit><quote>broad buttock, tender h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 298" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 298</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the spur that anger thrusts into his h.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 50.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 50, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>an a may catch your h. and you alone,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.136" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 136</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.136" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 136</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.128" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 128</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 2, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 2, 9</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 109</bibl>. Applied to men in contempt: <bibl n="shak. shr 2.406" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 406</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.137" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.6.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 6, 31</bibl> (used of an armour). <bibl n="shak. ham 5.1.186" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. V, 1, 186</bibl>.
